<recipe>
<title>
Creamy Chicken Enchilada Pasta
</title>
<details>

</details>
<ingredients>
1 tablespoon vegetable oil
1 white or yellow onion diced
3 cups cooked chicken shredded
4 ounce can diced green chiles
1 teaspoon paprika smoked or regular
15 ounce can chicken broth
1/2 cup fat-free half and half
2 tablespoons butter
2 tablespoons all-purpose flour
1 ½ cups low-fat sour cream or plain non-fat or low-fat Greek yogurt
3 oz . reduced-fat cream cheese
2 ½ cups Colby jack or Monterrey jack cheese shredded
12 ounces penne pasta cooked and drained
1/4 cup cilantro chopped
</ingredients>
<instructions>
Preheat oven to 350 F. Spray a 9x13-inch casserole dish with non-stick spray; set aside.
Heat 1 tablespoon canola oil in skillet over medium heat.
Add onion; sauté for 1 minute.
Add chicken, green chilies, and paprika; stir together.
Add 1/2 cup chicken broth; stir.
Add half-and-half and stir, allowing mixture to get warm. Turn off heat and set aside.
Meanwhile, in a separate saucepan, melt butter.
Once butter has melted, whisk in flour. Cook over medium heat for one minute.
Pour in remaining chicken broth. Whisk together and cook for another minute or two.
Reduce heat to low; stir in sour cream and cream cheese.
Add 1 ½ cups grated cheese and stir to melt.
Add salt and pepper as needed.
To assemble, spoon half of the cooked pasta into the casserole dish.
Pour half of the chicken mixture over the pasta.
Spoon the other half of the pasta over the chicken mixture.
Pour the remaining chicken mixture over the pasta.
Cover the pasta with all of the cheese sauce.
Bake, uncovered, for 20 minutes.
Top with remaining 1 cup of cheese. Return to the oven for 5 minutes, or until cheese is melted.
To serve, sprinkle generously with chopped cilantro.
</instructions>
</recipe>
